			<h2 style="margin-left: 15px">Why Join the LMC?</h2>

				<div class="col-md-6 col-xs-12 spaced-left">
					<h3>Benefits of Membership</h3>
					<ul>
						<li>Busy calendar of meets all over the country (and sometimes abroad) all with great walking, climbing, scrambling and mountaineering in the area. See more in the <a href="#meets">Meets</a> section.</li>
						<li>Social events including talks, the annual dinner, the summer bash and pub meets.</li>
						<li><a href="#discounts">Discounts</a> at The Big Depot and local and national retailers.</li>
						<li>BMC affiliate membership.</li>
						<li>Access to training courses.</li>
					</ul>
					<%= link_to "Application Form", application_path, class: "btn btn-lg user-btn" %>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-6 col-xs-12 spaced-right">
					<h3>Who Can Join?</h3>
					<p>Anyone interested in getting outdoors to go walking, climbing and mountaineering with other like minded people.</p>
					<p>We don't set limitations on experience to become a member, however we do expect you to be able to enjoy your chosen activity safely. You'll need to own the basic gear and have a basic knowledge to be able to take part, eg: for climbing you'll need a harness and shoes and know how to belay.</p>
					<p>If you want to climb but haven't ever done so before then we suggest a course at a climbing wall as a good starting point - The Leeds Wall offer such courses.</p>
					<p>Under 18s can join the club, however there are limitations on which meets under 18s can attend.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
